<unclassified>
A man can be barred from seeking a DNA blood test of a child to determine paternity if the mother has legal care and control of the child and refuses to give her permission, Mr Justice Wall ruled in the High Court. He said that it was up to Parliament to reform the legal situation, which had arisen from the phrasing of the Family Law Reform Act.

